Senior Backend Engineer Skill and Responsibility Checklist

Senior Backend Engineer: Responsibilities & Skill Checklist

Networking & Web Protocols

  • TCP/IP, DNS, TLS/SSL fundamentals and deep understanding of HTTP/HTTPS (methods, status codes, headers)theseniordev.com.

  • REST and GraphQL API design standards (OpenAPI/Swagger, versioning, status codes, pagination)linkedin.com.

  • RPC and real-time protocols (gRPC with Protobuf, WebSockets, HTTP/2/3) for high-performance service communicationlinkedin.com.

  • Reverse proxy and load balancing configuration (NGINX/HAProxy, CDNs) and network security (firewalls, CORS).

Programming Paradigms & Design Principles

  • Master Object-Oriented (OOP) and Functional programming paradigms (SOLID principles, classes/inheritance vs immutability/recursion)theseniordev.com.

  • Concurrency and parallelism models (multithreading, async/await, event loops, locks)linkedin.com.

  • Software design patterns (MVC, layered architecture, repository/factory/singleton, service mesh patterns)theseniordev.com.

  • Clean code practices: code reviews, refactoring, modularity, dependency injection, inversion of controltheseniordev.com.

  • Familiarity with programming paradigms beyond the mainstream (reactive/event-driven, functional reactive) and applying them as needed.

API Design & Integration

  • Develop and document robust APIs: RESTful services, GraphQL schemas, gRPC interfaces, with OpenAPI/Swagger specificationlinkedin.com.

  • API versioning and backward compatibility strategies (URI versioning, headers, content negotiation)linkedin.com.

  • Integrate third-party and internal services: calling external REST/SOAP APIs, handling webhooks, writing API clients/SDKs.

  • Implement authentication and authorization in APIs (OAuth2.0, JWT, OpenID Connect)linkedin.com.

  • Rate limiting, throttling, API gateways/proxies (e.g. Kong, AWS API Gateway) to manage trafficlinkedin.com.

  • API testing and monitoring (Postman, Swagger tests, automated API integration tests)nexalab.io.

Data Management & Databases

  • Design data models for relational (PostgreSQL, MySQL) and NoSQL databases (MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis)nexalab.iolinkedin.com.

  • Database schema design, normalization/denormalization, indexing and query optimizationlinkedin.comnexalab.io.

  • Transaction management and isolation levels (ACID guarantees) vs eventual consistency trade-offslinkedin.comtheseniordev.com.

  • High availability and scaling: replication, sharding/partitioning, clustering, database migrations and versioninglinkedin.comnexalab.io.

  • Caching layers and in-memory stores (Redis, Memcached) for performancelinkedin.com.

  • Database backup/restore, failover, disaster recovery and data durability measuresnexalab.io.

Security & Compliance

  • Authentication and authorization frameworks (OAuth2.0, JWT, role-based access control)linkedin.com.

  • Web security best practices: OWASP Top 10 (SQLi, XSS, CSRF, etc.), input validation/sanitization, secure defaults.

  • Data protection: encryption in transit (TLS) and at rest (AES, KMS), secure key management.

  • Secure coding practices: vulnerability scanning (SAST, dependency scanning), secrets management, GDPR/PCI/HIPAA compliance.

  • Implement and audit logging for security events, monitoring suspicious activities.

  • Follow internal and industry compliance standards, code reviews for security, and keep up with threat models.

Performance, Scalability & Reliability

  • Advanced caching strategies (application cache, CDN cache, HTTP caching) to reduce latencylinkedin.com.

  • Rate limiting, circuit breakers, bulkheads and backpressure to maintain service reliability under loadlinkedin.com.

  • Load balancing and autoscaling (horizontal scaling across instances or containers) for high traffic handlinglinkedin.com.

  • Profiling and optimizing code and queries (profilers, flame graphs, index tuning)4cornerresources.com.

  • Stress and performance testing (load testing with JMeter, Locust) to identify bottlenecks.

  • Chaos engineering and fault injection (breaker patterns) to test system resiliencelinkedin.com.

  • High availability design: failover strategies, multi-AZ/multi-region deployments, graceful degradation.

Architecture & Design Patterns

  • System architecture choices: monolith vs modular monolith vs microservices vs serverlesslinkedin.com.

  • Service-oriented and microservice patterns (API Gateway, BFF, circuit breakers, sagas).

  • Event-driven and message-driven architectures (event sourcing, CQRS).

  • Design patterns in distributed systems (observer, pub/sub, messaging).

  • Scalability considerations: CAP theorem, consistency vs availability trade-offstheseniordev.com.

Distributed Systems & Messaging

  • Message queues and streaming platforms (Kafka, RabbitMQ, AWS SQS/SNS) for asynchronous work.
